main event: A witness in Winnsboro, Texas spotted a peculiar object in the sky in August 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as two bright lights, white and amber in color, that were moving fast and at a high altitude.
The object was completely silent and appeared to be vibrating.
The object was observed for 3-5 seconds before disappearing over the horizon.
The witness was a commercial pilot and was familiar with seeing objects in the sky at all hours.
The witness said the object was traveling at an estimated speed of 1,000 to 1,500 miles per hour.
sighted object: two bright lights in the sky
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
